   "source": [
    "# 06: Demand Signal Detection via DeepSeek LLM\n",
    "===============================================\n",
    "\n",
    "**Objective:** Use DeepSeek to screen cleaned YouTube comments and identify demand signals\n",
    "related to **protective shell / case / cover** products across all categories\n",
    "(not limited to electronics).\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## What is a \"Demand Signal\"?\n",
    "\n",
    "A demand signal is any comment that reveals a user's **latent or explicit need** for a\n",
    "protective shell/case/cover product. Examples:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Signal Type | Description | Comment Example |\n",
    "|-------------|-------------|-----------------|\n",
    "| **Purchase Intent** | Explicit desire to buy | \"I need a hard case for my drone\" |\n",
    "| **Problem/Complaint** | Unmet need, frustration | \"My equipment keeps getting damaged\" |\n",
    "| **Comparison/Research** | Seeking the right option | \"Is a hard case or soft case better for...?\" |\n",
    "| **Usage Scenario** | Describes protection need | \"I travel a lot, need something shockproof\" |\n",
    "| **Wishful Thinking** | Wishes they had protection | \"Should have gotten a case for my...\" |\n",
    "\n",
    "**DeepSeek's role:** Classify each comment and explain *why* it contains a demand signal.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Scope Note\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook focuses on **protective shells/cases/covers** broadly:\n",
    "- Hard cases, soft cases, pouches, sleeves, covers\n",
    "- Camera bags, tool boxes, equipment cases\n",
    "- Travel organizers, packing cubes\n",
    "- DJ equipment cases, musical instrument cases\n",
    "- Any carrying/protective container for valuable items\n",
    "\n",
    "Not limited to electronics. Not limited to phone cases.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Pipeline Overview\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "cleaned_comments_linked.parquet\n",
    "    → Batch into groups of 20-30 comments\n",
    "    → DeepSeek API (few-shot classification)\n",
    "    → Parse JSON responses\n",
    "    → Save: comments + video_id + video_url + signal + reason\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 1. Setup & Configuration"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
