   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 4. DeepSeek Prompt Design\n",
    "\n",
    "We use a **few-shot classification** approach:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **System prompt** — defines what counts as a demand signal with examples\n",
    "2. **User prompt** — contains a batch of comments to classify\n",
    "3. **Output format** — structured JSON array\n",
    "\n",
    "### Demand Signal Taxonomy (for the LLM)\n",
    "\n",
    "| Label | Description |\n",
    "|-------|-------------|\n",
    "| `purchase_intent` | Explicit desire/intent to buy a protective case |\n",
    "| `problem_complaint` | Frustration about damage / lack of protection |\n",
    "| `comparison_research` | Asking about or comparing different cases |\n",
    "| `usage_scenario` | Describes a use case requiring protection |\n",
    "| `wishful_thinking` | Wishes they had / should have bought protection |\n",
    "| `supply_recommendation` | Recommends or praises a specific case |\n",
    "| `no_signal` | Does not indicate demand for protective cases |\n",
    "\n",
    "**Rule:** A comment is `no_signal` if it is:\n",
    "- A generic compliment (\"nice case!\")\n",
    "- A question about something unrelated to cases\n",
    "- Spam or nonsense\n",
    "- Only mentions cases in a negative/humorous non-purchase context"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ================================================================\n",
    "# SYSTEM PROMPT — Few-Shot Demand Signal Classifier\n",
    "# ================================================================\n",
    "\n",
    "SYSTEM_PROMPT = \"\"\"You are a demand signal classifier for consumer product research.\n",
    "\n",
    "TASK: Read each YouTube comment and determine whether it reveals a demand signal\n",
    "for a PROTECTIVE SHELL / CASE / COVER product.\n",
    "\n",
    "IMPORTANT SCOPE: Protective shells/cases/covers are not limited to electronics.\n",
    "They include: hard cases, soft cases, pouches, sleeves, bags, organizers,\n",
    "carrying cases, storage cases, travel cases, equipment cases, tool boxes,\n",
    "camera bags, instrument cases, DJ gear cases, packing cubes, etc.\n",
    "\n",
    "CLASSIFICATION LABELS:\n",
    "\n",
    "  1. purchase_intent — Explicit desire or plan to acquire a protective case.\n",
    "     Examples:\n",
    "       \"I need a hard case for my drone\"\n",
    "       \"Looking for a case that can protect my camera during travel\"\n",
    "       \"Just bought a new lens, need a case for it\"\n",
    "\n",
    "  2. problem_complaint — Expresses frustration about damage or lack of protection.\n",
    "     Examples:\n",
    "       \"My equipment keeps getting scratched\"\n",
    "       \"The foam padding is terrible, items arrived damaged\"\n",
    "       \"Dropped my camera and the lens broke, should have gotten a case\"\n",
    "\n",
    "  3. comparison_research — Actively comparing or researching protective cases.\n",
    "     Examples:\n",
    "       \"Is a hard case better than a soft case for outdoor photography?\"\n",
    "       \"Looking at the Nanuk vs. Pelican, which is more durable?\"\n",
    "       \"Which bag should I get for carrying my gaming laptop?\"\n",
    "\n",
    "  4. usage_scenario — Describes a specific use context that requires protection.\n",
    "     Examples:\n",
    "       \"I travel with my gear a lot and need something shockproof\"\n",
    "       \"This case is perfect for hiking and outdoor adventures\"\n",
    "       \"I use this organizer for my everyday carry items\"\n",
    "\n",
    "  5. wishful_thinking — Wishes they had bought or owned a protective case.\n",
    "     Examples:\n",
    "       \"I should have gotten a case for my Switch\"\n",
    "       \"Wish I had bought the hard case version\"\n",
    "       \"Would be nice if this came with a protective cover\"\n",
    "\n",
    "  6. supply_recommendation — Recommends or positively reviews a specific case product.\n",
    "     Examples:\n",
    "       \"This hard case saved my camera from a bad fall\"\n",
    "       \"Best protective case I've ever owned, highly recommend\"\n",
    "       \"The foam insert is perfectly cut, fits all my gear\"\n",
    "\n",
    "  7. no_signal — Does NOT indicate demand for protective cases.\n",
    "     Examples:\n",
    "       \"Nice video, thanks for sharing\"\n",
    "       \"LOL that was funny\"\n",
    "       \"Can you do a video on X instead?\"\n",
    "       \"I already have a case I like\"\n",
    "       \"What brand is the camera in this video?\"\n",
    "\n",
    "OUTPUT FORMAT: Return a JSON array, one object per comment.\n",
    "\n",
    "{\n",
    "  \"results\": [\n",
    "    {\n",
    "      \"comment_id\": \"<comment_id>\",\n",
    "      \"signal\": \"<label>\",\n",
    "      \"confidence\": <0.0-1.0>,\n",
    "      \"reason\": \"<2-4 sentence explanation of WHY this is or is not a demand signal>\"\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    ...\n",
    "  ]\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "RULES:\n",
    "- If a comment is in a language other than English, still analyze it.\n",
    "- If a comment is borderline, pick the most appropriate label and explain.\n",
    "- confidence is your self-assessed certainty from 0.0 to 1.0.\n",
    "- reason must specifically mention what in the comment triggered the signal label.\n",
    "- Only output valid JSON. No markdown, no explanation outside the JSON.\n",
    "\"\"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"System prompt loaded.\\n\")\n",
    "print(SYSTEM_PROMPT[:500] + \"...\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 5. Batch Processing Helper"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import openai  # DeepSeek uses OpenAI-compatible API\n",
    "\n",
    "CLIENT = openai.OpenAI(\n",
    "    api_key=os.environ['DEEPSEEK_API_KEY'],\n",
    "    base_url=\"https://api.deepseek.com/v1\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "def build_user_prompt(batch_df):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Build the user prompt containing a batch of comments.\"\"\"\n",
    "    lines = []\n",
    "    for _, row in batch_df.iterrows():\n",
    "        comment_id = str(row['comment_id'])\n",
    "        text = str(row['text_original']).strip()\n",
    "        video_title = str(row.get('title', 'N/A'))[:80]\n",
    "        lines.append(\n",
    f\"[Comment ID: {comment_id}] [Video: {video_title}]\\n{text}\"\n",
    "        )\n",
    "    return \"\\n\\n\".join(lines)\n",
    "\n",
    "def call_deepseek_batch(batch_df, model=\"deepseek-chat\", max_retries=3):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Call DeepSeek API for a batch of comments.\"\"\"\n",
    "    user_prompt = build_user_prompt(batch_df)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for attempt in range(max_retries):\n",
    "        try:\n",
    "            response = CLIENT.chat.completions.create(\n",
    "                model=model,\n",
    "                messages=[\n",
    "                    {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": SYSTEM_PROMPT},\n",
    "                    {\"role\": \"user\",   \"content\": user_prompt},\n",
    "                ],\n",
    "                temperature=0.1,   # Low temp for consistent classification\n",
    "                max_tokens=4096,\n",
    "            )\n",
    "            raw = response.choices[0].message.content.strip()\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Try to extract JSON from the response\n",
    "            # Sometimes model wraps in ```json ... ```\n",
    "            json_match = re.search(r'\\[.*\\]', raw, re.DOTALL)\n",
    "            if json_match:\n",
    "                parsed = json.loads(json_match.group())\n",
    "            else:\n",
    "                parsed = json.loads(raw)\n",
    "            \n",
    "            return parsed\n",
    "        except json.JSONDecodeError as e:\n",
    "            print(f\"  [Attempt {attempt+1}] JSON parse error: {e}\")\n",
    "            if attempt < max_retries - 1:\n",
    "                time.sleep(2 ** attempt)\n",
    "        except Exception as e:\n",
    "            print(f\"  [Attempt {attempt+1}] API error: {e}\")\n",
    "            if attempt < max_retries - 1:\n",
    "                time.sleep(2 ** attempt)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return None  # All retries failed\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"API helper functions ready.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 6. Run Classification (Batched)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Settings:**\n",
    "- `BATCH_SIZE = 20` — comments per API call (keep it manageable for detailed reasoning)\n",
    "- `SAVE_EVERY = 5` — save checkpoint every N batches\n",
    "- `RATE_LIMIT_DELAY = 1.5` — seconds between calls (stay well within rate limits)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Estimated cost:** ~$0.001 per 100 comments (DeepSeek-chat, 20 comments/batch)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ================================================================\n",
    "# Processing settings\n",
    "# ================================================================\n",
    "\n",
    "BATCH_SIZE         = 20        # comments per API call\n",
    "SAVE_EVERY         = 5         # save checkpoint every N batches\n",
    "RATE_LIMIT_DELAY   = 1.5       # seconds between API calls\n",
    "MODEL_NAME         = \"deepseek-chat\"  # or \"deepseek-coder\" if preferred\n",
    "\n",
    "N = len(df_work)\n",
    "n_batches = (N + BATCH_SIZE - 1) // BATCH_SIZE\n",
    "print(f\"Total comments : {N:,}\")\n",
    f\"Batch size     : {BATCH_SIZE}\"\n",
    f\"Total batches  : {n_batches:,}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ================================================================\n",
    "# Main classification loop\n",
    "# ================================================================\n",
    "\n",
    "all_results = []          # collected results\n",
    "failed_batches = []      # track batches that failed\n",
    "start_time = time.time()\n",
    "\n",
    "for batch_idx in tqdm(range(n_batches), desc=\"Classifying batches\"):\n",
    "    start = batch_idx * BATCH_SIZE\n",
    "    end   = min(start + BATCH_SIZE, N)\n",
    "    batch_df = df_work.iloc[start:end].reset_index(drop=True)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    result = call_deepseek_batch(batch_df, model=MODEL_NAME)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if result is not None:\n",
    "        all_results.extend(result.get('results', []))\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        failed_batches.append(batch_idx)\n",
    "        # Mark failed comment_ids\n",
    "        for _, row in batch_df.iterrows():\n",
    "            all_results.append({\n",
    "                'comment_id': str(row['comment_id']),\n",
    "                'signal': 'error',\n",
    "                'confidence': 0.0,\n",
    "                'reason': 'API call failed after retries'\n",
    "            })\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Progress logging every 10 batches\n",
    "    if (batch_idx + 1) % 10 == 0:\n",
    "        elapsed = time.time() - start_time\n",
    "        eta = (elapsed / (batch_idx + 1)) * (n_batches - batch_idx - 1)\n",
    "        print(f\"\\n  [{batch_idx+1}/{n_batches}] Done: {len(all_results):,} results | ETA: {eta:.0f}s | Failed: {len(failed_batches)}\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Checkpoint save\n",
    "    if (batch_idx + 1) % SAVE_EVERY == 0:\n",
    "        ckpt_path = CHECKPOINT_DIR / f\"batch_{batch_idx+1}_checkpoint.json\"\n",
    "        with open(ckpt_path, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n",
    "            json.dump(all_results, f, ensure_ascii=False)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Respect rate limits\n",
    "    time.sleep(RATE_LIMIT_DELAY)\n",
    "\n",
    "elapsed_total = time.time() - start_time\n",
    "print(f\"\\n{'='*60}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Classification complete!\")\n",
    "print(f\"Total time     : {elapsed_total:.1f}s\")\n",
    "print(f\"Total results  : {len(all_results):,}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Failed batches : {len(failed_batches)}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 7. Merge Results & Build Output Dataset"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Convert results to DataFrame\n",
    "results_df = pd.DataFrame(all_results)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Merge with original data\n",
    "df_work['_comment_id'] = df_work['comment_id'].astype(str)\n",
    "results_df['comment_id'] = results_df['comment_id'].astype(str)\n",
    "\n",
    "df_output = df_work.merge(\n",
    "    results_df[['comment_id', 'signal', 'confidence', 'reason']],\n",
    "    on='comment_id',\n",
    "    how='left'\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Drop helper column\n",
    "df_output = df_output.drop(columns=['_comment_id'])\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Output rows: {len(df_output):,}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Columns: {df_output.columns.tolist()}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Quick sanity check\n",
    "print(\"\\nSignal distribution:\")\n",
    "print(df_output['signal'].value_counts())\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nConfidence stats (non-error):\")\n",
    "valid = df_output[df_output['signal'] != 'error']\n",
    "print(valid['confidence'].describe())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 8. Filter to Demand Signal Comments Only"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Keep only comments with actual demand signals\n",
    "DEMAND_SIGNALS = [\n",
    "    'purchase_intent',\n",
    "    'problem_complaint',\n",
    "    'comparison_research',\n",
    "    'usage_scenario',\n",
    "    'wishful_thinking',\n",
    "    'supply_recommendation',\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "df_demand = df_output[df_output['signal'].isin(DEMAND_SIGNALS)].copy()\n",
    "print(f\"Comments with demand signals: {len(df_demand):,} / {len(df_output):,} ({100*len(df_demand)/len(df_output):.1f}%)\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nSignal breakdown:\")\n",
    "print(df_demand['signal'].value_counts())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 9. Final Output Columns"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Select final output columns\n",
    "FINAL_COLS = [\n",
    "    'comment_id',\n",
    "    'video_id',\n",
    "    'video_url',\n",
    "    'text_original',\n",
    "    'signal',\n",
    "    'confidence',\n",
    "    'reason',\n",
    "    'title',           # video title\n",
    "    'channel_title',\n",
    "    'comment_like_count',\n",
    "    'priority_level',  # from rule-based pre-filter\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "available_final = [c for c in FINAL_COLS if c in df_demand.columns]\n",
    "df_final = df_demand[available_final].copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Rename for clarity\n",
    "df_final = df_final.rename(columns={\n",
    "    'text_original': 'comment_text',\n",
    "    'title':         'video_title',\n",
    "})\n",
    "\n",
    "# Sort by confidence descending\n",
    "df_final = df_final.sort_values('confidence', ascending=False).reset_index(drop=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Final dataset: {len(df_final):,} demand signal comments\")\n",
    "print(df_final.head(3).to_string())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 10. Save Results"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "timestamp = time.strftime(\"%Y%m%d_%H%M%S\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Save full dataset (all comments + classification)\n",
    "full_parquet = OUTPUT_DIR / f\"demand_signals_full_{timestamp}.parquet\"\n",
    "full_csv     = OUTPUT_DIR / f\"demand_signals_full_{timestamp}.csv\"\n",
